What is bootstrap?
- Bootstrap is a library used to build UI rapidly.
- It provides pre-defined components and templates that allow to build responsive interfaces rapidly.

Bootstrap [5]

Setup Bootstrap for the project:

1.
    > npm install bootstrap  bootstrap-icons --save

2. Link the following files to the page

 <link rel="stylesheet" href="../node_modules/bootstrap-icons/font/bootstrap-icons.css">
 <link rel="stylesheet" href="../node_modules/bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.css">
 <script src="../node_modules/bootstrap/dist/js/bootstrap.bundle.js"> </script>

Note: Bootstrap makes the page interactive and responsive. It has default styles to apply.

